</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
<m:mo> ⇒ </m:mo> 
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mo> = </m:mo>
<m:mi> ω </m:mi>
<m:mo> x </m:mo>
<m:mfrac>
<m:mrow>
<m:mn> 3 </m:mn>
<m:mi> R </m:mi>
</m:mrow>
<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
</m:mfrac>
<m:mo> = </m:mo>
<m:mfrac>
<m:mrow>
<m:mn> 3 </m:mn>
<m:mi> ω </m:mi>
<m:mi> R </m:mi>
</m:mrow>
<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
</m:mfrac>
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-36a">
(ii) The observer is moving with velocity “ωR/2” in the direction of rolling. Thus, relative velocity of the particle with respect to observer is :
</para>
